  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StepSolver<java.util.List<Expression>>, java.lang.Cloneable

    @Beta
public class SelectExpressionsSatisfyingComparisonStepSolver
extends AbstractSelectionStepSolver
    A context-dependent problem step solver deciding which in a set of expressions that satisfy a comparison according to a given functor and bound.

    Unlike many step solvers finding Expression-typed solutions, this one is not an extension of ExpressionStepSolver because it extends AbstractExpressionsSequenceStepSolver, which does not necessarily have Expression-typed solutions. This has the disadvantage of requiring the use of generic StepSolver#SolverStep, instead of its more common specialization ExpressionStepSolver#SolverStep.
